they don't invite me. Literally.

41:57.557 --> 41:59.309
- They run away from me.
- No. Listen to me.

41:59.476 --> 42:00.852
They're leery of men.
That's all.

42:01.019 --> 42:02.604
Especially married men
with children.

42:02.771 --> 42:05.565
Oh. I'm not exactly married.

42:05.732 --> 42:07.651
Am I?

42:08.818 --> 42:10.779
We're a family, aren't we?

42:12.739 --> 42:14.324
- Maggie...
- What?

42:14.491 --> 42:16.451
Is this really
how we're gonna do it?

42:16.618 --> 42:18.411
You're gonna
come home every weekend

42:18.578 --> 42:20.956
and then take up residence
on the sofa?

42:22.499 --> 42:24.251
For now.

42:24.417 --> 42:26.336
- Maggie...
- What?

42:26.503 --> 42:30.131
We haven't slept together
since before my breakdown.

42:30.298 --> 42:32.717
I'm dying!

42:32.884 --> 42:35.720
You're dying too.
You just don't realise it.

42:35.887 --> 42:38.014
- Cam, I just...
- Maggie...

42:38.181 --> 42:42.143
Oh... Can we... Can we please
just get through this phase?

42:42.310 --> 42:44.396
Just let's just get through
this phase,

42:44.563 --> 42:46.439
and then we'll see
how it goes.

42:46.606 --> 42:48.166
- And then what happens?
- I don't know.

42:48.316 --> 42:50.151
What's the end?
You move back in here...

42:50.318 --> 42:52.118
- I don't know.
- And then what happens to us?

42:52.237 --> 42:53.780
- I don't know!
- Where do I go?

42:53.947 --> 42:55.657
No. I don't know.

42:55.824 --> 42:57.659
All I know
is that it's gonna take

42:57.826 --> 43:01.538
steady, sustained effort.

43:01.705 --> 43:04.958
Yes. Sexy, sexy answer.

43:07.419 --> 43:10.171
It's an honest, honest answer.

43:11.965 --> 43:14.259
So, what's this?
Some big test? I mean...

43:14.426 --> 43:17.971
No. Don't look at it that way.
You hate tests.

43:18.138 --> 43:20.932
Not if this is
what's on the test.

43:37.324 --> 43:39.326
Coolant's a little low.

43:46.416 --> 43:48.585
Uneven wear on the tyres.

43:52.339 --> 43:53.882
Lock sticks.

43:56.051 --> 43:59.387
- There's no floor!
- But it's got a great engine.

44:00.764 --> 44:02.204
There's, uh...
there's no floor here.

44:02.349 --> 44:04.267
And... and the roof
is rotted out.

44:04.434 --> 44:07.228
I have two small children.
It's dangerous.

44:07.395 --> 44:10.357
What do you say
we close at 300 cash?

44:11.608 --> 44:13.151
You deal with the wagon.

44:22.744 --> 44:24.496
Daddy, Amelia's crying.

44:24.663 --> 44:27.207
- You always cry.
- Not anymore.

44:27.374 --> 44:30.085
- I vowed never to cry again.
- What's wrong, darling?

44:30.251 --> 44:35.674
What's gonna happen to the wagon?
Nobody's gonna want it.

44:35.840 --> 44:37.842
I thought you were crying
because this car sucks.

44:38.009 --> 44:40.136
That car sucked too.

45:35.400 --> 45:37.360
Remember to speak up, girls.

45:37.527 --> 45:39.571
Your great-grandmother
was born in 1888.

45:42.282 --> 45:46.745
I propose a game of Crazy Eights
after lunch.

45:46.911 --> 45:49.914
- Yeah!
- We don't say 'yeah', dear.

45:50.081 --> 45:52.083
- We say 'yes'.
- Thank you, Gaga.

45:52.250 --> 45:54.461
That's a battle
their mother keeps fighting.

45:54.627 --> 45:57.088
- And how is their mother?
- She's very well.

45:57.255 --> 45:58.895
She comes every weekend,
but this weekend,

45:59.007 --> 46:02.510
she stayed in the city
to study for her exams.

46:02.677 --> 46:05.513
But we're muddling through.
Aren't we, girls? Hm.

46:05.680 --> 46:08.349
A.J., will you please tell Betty
that the roast is divine?

46:08.516 --> 46:10.018
Yes, sir.

46:10.185 --> 46:12.604
Do you girls find it unusual

46:12.771 --> 46:14.731
that your mother
is in New York?

46:14.898 --> 46:16.733
She wants to have
more career opportunities.

46:16.900 --> 46:19.068
Mommy says
women can do anything.

46:19.235 --> 46:21.863
She's quite a striver,
isn't she?

46:22.030 --> 46:24.032
We prefer the word 'fighter'.

46:27.494 --> 46:29.871
I'm going
to go work on the car.

46:30.038 --> 46:32.332
