it has no floor.

46:32.499 --> 46:34.334
It had no floor.

46:34.501 --> 46:36.141
I scavenged these
from your kitchen vault.

46:36.252 --> 46:38.087
Betty said I could have them.

46:38.254 --> 46:40.965
- Cookie sheets?
- You still can't step on them.

46:41.132 --> 46:43.885
But they'll certainly keep out
the cold and detritus.

46:44.052 --> 46:46.721
Cam, I'm so proud of you

46:46.888 --> 46:50.141
for taking care of these
darling girls all by yourself.

46:50.308 --> 46:51.976
Thank you, Gaga.

46:52.143 --> 46:54.938
I'm mostly using the Lincoln
these days.

46:55.104 --> 46:57.649
I want you
to have the Bentley.

46:57.816 --> 47:00.360
- The Bentley?
- Mmm.

47:02.445 --> 47:04.447
There are trays
where we could eat.

47:04.614 --> 47:06.491
Could we eat dinner
in the car?

47:08.243 --> 47:12.038
All the windows work.
There's a floor!

47:12.205 --> 47:15.500
It smells so good.

47:15.667 --> 47:17.544
Gaga, we live in
a rent-controlled apartment.

47:17.710 --> 47:20.255
I know that.
I pay your rent.

47:20.421 --> 47:24.342
- And we're very grateful for it.
- It's dirt-cheap.

47:24.509 --> 47:27.470
But the point is I can't even
afford to maintain the Bentley.

47:27.637 --> 47:29.973
I can't even afford
to fill its gas tank.

47:30.139 --> 47:32.350
If you're asking me
for gas money...

47:32.517 --> 47:35.478
No, Gaga,
I'm not asking for gas money.

47:37.647 --> 47:41.442
The girls are both
phenomenal students.

47:41.609 --> 47:44.863
And they're not being challenged
where they are right now.

47:45.029 --> 47:47.198
And if you really
wanted to help,

47:47.365 --> 47:50.243
they would flourish
in a private school.

47:51.619 --> 47:55.957
I don't think that's teaching
the girls a very good lesson.

47:56.124 --> 47:57.834
Do you?

48:03.172 --> 48:05.008
No, I suppose not.

48:15.852 --> 48:18.229
Look, I'm sorry
I didn't take the Bentley.

48:18.396 --> 48:21.316
It didn't make any sense.
I know you're disappointed.

48:21.482 --> 48:23.860
You should have taken it
and sold it

48:24.027 --> 48:26.696
and then bought a crepe cart
and made lots of money

48:26.863 --> 48:28.573
and then we wouldn't
be so poor.

48:28.740 --> 48:30.617
Sweetheart,
although crepes are delicious,

48:30.783 --> 48:32.744
they're not exactly the goldmine
that you think they are,

48:32.911 --> 48:34.287
especially during a recession.

48:34.454 --> 48:37.624
Well, then, we could have
sold the Bentley

48:37.790 --> 48:39.459
and just had some money.

48:39.626 --> 48:41.377
Gaga would have never let me
sell that car.

48:41.544 --> 48:43.880
- She was giving it to you.
- It doesn't work like that.

48:44.047 --> 48:46.215
It's hard to explain.

48:46.382 --> 48:48.134
It was our one chance
to have something

48:48.301 --> 48:50.178
that other people might want.

48:50.345 --> 48:52.055
Nobody wants what we have.

48:59.020 --> 49:00.730
Daddy did something
so amazing.

49:00.897 --> 49:02.607
He did?

49:02.774 --> 49:04.534
Guess what I paid
for this parking spot.

49:04.692 --> 49:06.986
- Oh, God!
- Absolutely nothing.

49:07.153 --> 49:10.239
Well...
You get what you pay for.

49:10.406 --> 49:12.075
We have a surprise for you.

49:12.241 --> 49:14.577
- OK.
- That's Jock! That's our dog!

49:14.744 --> 49:17.025
- Daddy got him for us!
- Amelia named him!

49:20.708 --> 49:23.086
OK. Why... why
is he acting this way?

49:23.252 --> 49:25.046
He was abused
by his last owner.

49:25.213 --> 49:27.423
So any time Daddy leaves him,
he gets really upset.

49:27.590 --> 49:29.592
Because he loves Daddy.
'Cause Daddy saved him.

49:29.759 --> 49:31.886
We're working on it.

49:33.346 --> 49:34.973
And this is the new car?

49:35.139 --> 49:36.891
It was abused
by its last owner.

49:37.058 --> 49:39.852
But Daddy saved it.

49:40.019 --> 49:41.646
- Who's a good boy?
- Jock!

49:41.813 --> 49:43.439
- Jock, no!
- Wait!

49:43.606 --> 49:45.942
- Wait! Girls!
- Jock! Jock!

49:46.109 --> 49:48.277
- Jock! Come back!
- No!

49:48.444 --> 49:49.988
Don't eat that!

49:56.327 --> 49:59.330
- That's it, Little! Whoa!
- Whoa!

49:59.497 --> 50:01.040
Get up!

50:03.376 --> 50:05.753
Get in there!
Get in there like you mean it!

50:07.880 --> 50:09.424
Ah!

50:09.590 --> 50:11.050
Yes!

50:11.217 --> 50:13.302
Hey.

50:13.469 --> 50:15.429
Don't those two little girls
live in our building?

50:15.555 --> 50:17.390
Yeah, but they're really mean.

50:17.557 --> 50:20.393
Mean? They're wearing
matching pink pompom hats.

50:20.560 --> 50:22.353
How mean can they be?

50:22.520 --> 50:24.480
Hey! Little girls!

50:24.647 --> 50:26.482
Little boy!

50:26.649 --> 50:28.818
Come.
Come play basketball with us.

50:28.985 --> 50:30.862
- Are they mean?
- Mm-hm.

50:48.129 --> 50:49.630
That's it, Amelia.
Put pressure on him.

50:49.797 --> 50:51.674
Get your hands in there!

50:57.305 --> 51:00.183
Hands up, Amelia! Hands up!

51:02.894 --> 51:04.437
Alright, good job.

51:04.604 --> 51:06.397
Oh, yes!

51:09.484 --> 51:12.278
Those kids seem nice.
We should invite them over sometime.

51:12.445 --> 51:14.072
No way!

51:14.238 --> 51:16.365
I'd rather die than have people
into our shithole.

51:17.909 --> 51:19.452
They crush my soul.

